        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 6:03PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 602 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pisgah, or 9 miles east of Canton, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Farmhaven and Sharon around 610 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
